Unified Schema — Contract v1
This is the single agreed format that all four accounting systems (Gilde, Yuki, Exact, Snelstart) are translated into.
Every adapter (ingest_gilde, ingest_yuki, ingest_exact, ingest_snelstart) must take its system's native export and return rows that obey exactly this schema. Nothing downstream (driver model, scenario engine, role views) knows anything about the native formats — it only ever sees this table.

Frozen once, built against by all three. Once this is agreed, Person B and Person C build against it using synthetic rows while Person A reconciles the real data underneath. Do not change column names or meanings without telling the whole team.


The grain
One row = one financial event line, at transaction grain. An invoice with three lines is three rows. A bank payment is one row. WIP and open commitments are also rows (see status).
Accrual events (invoice issued, work recognised) and cash events (money moved / predicted to move) are both represented, distinguished by status. Never collapse them into a single "transaction" — the forecast depends on knowing what has not yet happened.

